Seacoast Church - Columbia
September 7 at 1:50 PM ¬∑

// MAKE A DIFFERENCE MONDAY //

This summer, we asked our church to join us as we partnered with Killian Elementary to bless students who need it most in this season.

And last week, our staff presented a $2500 check and 2500 N-95 masks to Principal Stacey Franklin. He was blown away by the generosity of our church!

Shoutout to those who gave to this worthy project. We are thankful for you!

#makeadifference #seacoastchurch #seacoastcolumbia

Good evening.
This is Dawn MacAdams, the Coordinator of Health Services. As the parent of kindergartner, did you know your child is required to have Two (2) Hepatitis A shots prior to entering Kindergarten. Yes, it‚Äôs true. These shots will help protect your child from Hepatitis A. Please visit https://scdhec.gov/index.php/health/vaccinations/childcare-school-vaccine-requirements to read about South Carolina Immunization requirements.

Call your physician today to schedule an appointment. If you don't have a regular physician, you can call DHEC at 1-855-472-3432 to schedule an appointment. Did I mention these shots are required for school?
If your child has already received Two Hepatitis A shots, please take a copy of their shot record to the school nurse.

Your child will be unable to attend school without proof of having received Two (2) Hepatitis A shots. Please contact your child‚Äôs school nurse if you need further assistance.

Thank you and good night.

DISTRICT FILLS THREE PRINCIPAL POSITIONS!

Richland School District Two is announcing the selections of three principals to fill elementary, middle and high school positions. At a regularly scheduled board meeting Tuesday, August 11, 2020, Superintendent Dr. Baron R. Davis recommended and the Richland Two Board of Trustees approved the selection of Shannon Holland as principal of Bethel-Hanberry Elementary School, Dr. Richard Griffin as principal of Kelly Mill Med Pro Middle School and Mark Sims as principal of Richland Northeast High School.

The principals will begin transitioning to their new positions immediately and officially assume leadership October 1, 2020.

Read more here: https://www.richland2.org/News/DISTRICT-FILLS-THREE-PRINCIPAL-POSITIONS

Congrats from all of us!
#PremierStartsHere

The Richland Two family is deeply saddened by the sudden passing of Calvin ‚ÄúChip‚Äù Jackson. Mr. Jackson served on the Richland School District Two Board of Trustees for eight years. He was elected to the school board in 2008 and re-elected in 2012, serving two terms as chairman.

‚ÄúMr. Jackson was a stalwart leader of public education and made positive impacts on the lives of many students, their families and our community,‚Äù said Richland Two Superintendent Dr. Baron R. Davis. ‚ÄúWhile he will be deeply missed, his dedication will never be forgotten. I will always remember the gentleness of his manner and fierceness of his conviction to make a difference in our community.‚Äù

We honor Mr. Jackson's legacy and impact on the Richland Two community.

FOUR RICHLAND TWO EDUCATORS EARN EMERGING LEADER DISTINCTION!

Are great leaders born or made? While arguments are often given for both sides, there‚Äôs no arguing Richland School District Two has several educators who are on a pathway to becoming better leaders. The South Carolina ASCD has selected Dr. Deborah Bennett, Kelley Dinkins, Kristen Eubanks, and Brandon Ross for its 2020-2021 Emerging Leaders Program.

The SCASCD Emerging Leaders Program seeks to empower educators to achieve excellence in learning, teaching, and leading so that every child is healthy, safe, engaged, supported, and challenged. According to SCASCD, emerging leaders participate in various networking opportunities and become part of a select pool of educators with exclusive access to opportunities to expand their professional reach.

Congratulations from all of us at Richland Two! #PremierStartsHere

More here: http://ow.ly/Lc4L50ATyAv

shared_text:
Summit Parkway Middle School
August 5 at 12:30 AM ¬∑

To inspire, to inform, and to learn are Kromuel Alcantara's goals as he continues his program being an international teacher from the Philippines here in the United States. He earned a Bachelor's Degree in Secondary Education major in English from the University of Southern Mindanao, Philippines, a Master's Degree in Language Teaching-English, and is currently pursuing a Doctorate in Education major in English in the same university. In his tenth year of teaching, Mr. Alcantara will be teaching 7th Grade English Language Arts at Summit Parkway Middle School. During his first year of teaching here in the US, he was inspired by the words of Mr. Craig Boykin when he said "Students put up walls, not to keep educators out but to see which educator cares enough to break them down."

In South Carolina, young adults between the ages of 21-30 currently make up 22% of all confirmed cases of Covid-19 and those ages 11-20 make up 11%.

A mask that covers the nose and mouth collects and traps respiratory droplets that spread when a person breathes, talks, coughs or sneezes. Masking up reduces the amount of virus in the air but not all of it, which is why it is also recommended that we practice social distancing.

SC DHEC has created COVID-19 mask content to encourage friends and followers to wear a face covering in public, which can be found at scdhec.gov/staySCstrong.

George Floyd‚Äôs brutal death ignited weeks of protests in every American city. While the crisis is national, change will happen at the local level. Our panel will amplify voices from a myriad of experiences and backgrounds, and explore immediate solutions for the systemic issues in our police departments and other local institutions.

"Breaking Point: Tackling Systemic Racism in South Carolina" will focus on the meaningful reforms needed in South Carolina. The forum will be held on the fifth anniversary of the Confederate flag's removal from the State House grounds. Our panelists will help us understand race issues in South Carolina and the policy changes needed in law enforcement and education.

The safety of our students and employees is our top priority. Each school, center, transportation hub and administrative office will have an electrostatic sprayer that our custodial services partner, Service Solutions, will use to sanitize surfaces daily.

Buses will be sanitized more often. The electrostatic process disinfects surfaces that it isn't practical to spray and wipe.

Touchpoints like door handles will be sanitized throughout the day. The electrostatic sprayers will only be used when students are not present.

This week for #futurechefsfriday, we're sharing the recipe for Monsta Pizza from Kyle Foster at Bethel-Hanberry Elementary. Kyle's vegetarian recipe stood out to the selection committee for it's unique take on a school lunch favorite.

Monsta Pizza

Ingredients:

14 oz shredded mozzarella
2 tbsp cream cheese
¬æ c almond flour
1 egg
¬Ω tsp salt
Olive oil
¬Ω tsp oregano
8 oz Morningstar sausage
¬º c green pepper
¬º c red pepper
¬º c yellow pepper
¬Ω c unsweetened tomato sauce
¬º c kale

Directions:

-Heat oven to 400
-Heat 6 oz mozzarella and cream cheese in nonstick pan
-Stir until melted together
-Add almond flour, egg and salt and mix well
-Moisten hands with olive oil and flatten dough on parchment paper
-Bake for 10-15 min until golden brown and remove from oven
-While crust is baking, saut√© sausage and peppers in olive oil
-Spread thin layer of sauce on crust
-Top with sausage, peppers and remaining mozzarella
-Bake for 10-15 min until cheese has melted
-Sprinkle with oregano

post_text: Surinamese music is an interesting mixture between indigenous South American rhythms, international European and North American trends. post_text: Haiti covers 10,714 square miles. It is located in the subtropics on the western third of Hispaniola, the second largest island in the Caribbean, which it shares with the Spanish-speaking Dominican Republic. The neighboring islands include Cuba, Jamaica, and Puerto Rico. Three-quarters of the terrain is mountainous; the highest peak is the Pic la Selle. Over 80 percent of the population resided in rural areas, and today, over 60 percent continue to live in provincial villages, hamlets, and homesteads scattered across the rural landscape. #CaribbeanHeritageMonth #R2DMI

Richland School District Two Nutrition - Sodexo
June 15 at 1:50 PM ¬∑

Messages like this, about our awesome Bethel-Hanberry Elementary crew, make it all worth it.

"I just had to take some time this evening to tell you about your amazing staff. Because my children insist on eating lunch from home I gave it no thought of getting the lunches provided by the district during this closure. One of my neighbors encouraged me to get it anyway to help me not have to prepare lunches every day. I have always been blessed to work from home, but working from home with [four children] was no picnic. I started going and it became my daily getaway driving to the school. Mrs. Helen and Mr. Carl were exceptional sights to see every day. For me they provided more than lunches. They provided friendly adult conversation, smiles in their eyes behind the mask and a laugh. They were doing more than their job, they were instilling kindness in a way the world could learn from at a time like this. These people have been my front line heroes, my essential workers and I appreciate them so much!"

‚ÄúLearning support staff rely on her insight and support because she has such excellent knowledge of our students and the impact their health concerns have on their academic success,‚Äù Barber said. ‚ÄúShe is an integral member of the learning support team and goes above and beyond to meet each student‚Äôs individual needs.‚Äù

post_text: An enjoyable Hawaiian custom is the flower lei. Custom dictates that a lei should be offered graciously with a kiss & removed only in private. It's considered rude to remove a lei once it's accepted in view of anyone, but especially of the person(s) who gave it to you.

post_text: Pakistani cuisine has affinities with that of India. Curry dishes are common, as are a variety of vegetables, including potatoes, eggplant, & okra. Each region (and household) has its preferred mixture of spices - or masala. Yogurt is a common ingredient. #AAPIHeritageMonth

post_text: Filipino is the official language of the Philippines, which primarily consists of Tagalog with other Philippine languages. English is the most common other language and is taught in schools. Many businesses also use it as the common language. #AAPIHeritageMonth #R2DMI

post_text: Traditional Filipino culture is comprised with a blend of Spanish Catholic traditions, along with influences from America and other parts of Asia. The Filipinos are family oriented and often religious with an appreciation for art, fashion, music and food. #AAPIHeritageMonth

post_text: Spring in Japan can only mean one thing: cherry blossom. The cherry blossom (or sakura) "front" sweeps along the length of the country each year, beginning with Okinawa in the far south in February & working its way along Japan to northern Hokkaido in May. #AAPIHeritageMonth

post_text: Seoul is the capital & most important city of South Korea. It could easily be compared to New York City. There are also five other major cities: Pusan, Inchon, Kwangju, Taejon & Taegu. Seoul is a highly populated city with 11 million people. #AAPIHeritageMonth

post_text: The Golden age of Cambodia was between the 9th & 14th century (the Angkor period), in which it was a prosperous empire over inland SE Asia. Cambodia's unparalleled achievements in art, architectures, music, & dance have greatly influenced neighboring kingdoms, Thailand & Laos.

post_text: Kalpana Chawla (March 17, 1962 ‚Äì February 1, 2003) was an American astronaut, engineer, and the first woman of Indian origin to go to space. She first flew on Space Shuttle Columbia in 1997 as a mission specialist and primary robotic arm operator. #AAPIHeritageMonth #R2DMI

post_text: A 3-day festival in Cambodia is the Water Festival (Festival of the Reversing Current). In late Oct or early Nov, it marks the reversal of the Tonle Sap River so it flows south into the Mekong River. Festival highlight: boat races held in Phnom Penh. #AAPIHeritageMonth
